<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,986,2092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,749,986,1013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">
Nomenclatural notes on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pampanini" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[425,749,986,1013]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" form="somaliensis" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="marmorata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[425,586,987,1013]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
f. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[615,749,986,1013]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
:—Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Pampanini, R." box="[896,1131,986,1013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="51 - 56" refId="ref9072" refString="Pampanini, R. (1909 [Febbraio]) Alcune Kalanchoe della Eritrea. Bullettino della SocietaI Botanica Italiana 1909 (2): 51 - 56. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 8551309  page / 345 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1909">Pampanini (1909: 53</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pampanini, R." box="[1142,1257,986,1013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="394 - 416" refId="ref9124" refString="Pampanini, R. (1911 [10 Juni]) 689. Kalanchoe marmorata Baker forma somaliensis (Hook. f. [sic, Baker]) Pampanini, p. 405. In: Anonymous. XCI. Vermischte neue Diagnosen. Repertorium specierum novarum regni vegetabilis 9 (217 / 221): 394 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19110092320" type="journal article" year="1911">1911: 405</bibRefCitation>
), as well as, later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen, H." box="[136,377,1022,1048]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" refId="ref8443" refString="Jacobsen, H. (1977) Lexicon of succulent plants. Short descriptions, habitats and synonymy of succulent plants other than Cactaceae. Revised and enlarged 2 nd edn. Blandford Press, Poole, Dorset, 682 pp." type="book" year="1977">Jacobsen (1977: 289)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen, H." box="[433,677,1022,1049]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="465 - 864" refId="ref8485" refString="Jacobsen, H. (1986) A handbook of succulent plants. Descriptions, synonyms and cultural details for succulents other than Cactaceae. Vol. II. Ficus to Zygophyllum. Blandford Press, Poole, Dorset, pp. 465 - 864." type="book chapter" year="1986">Jacobsen (1986: 629)</bibRefCitation>
, give the author citation of the basionym of the forma he recognised as “Hook. f.”, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1895" box="[298,461,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[298,461,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, J. G." box="[784,992,1058,1085]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="211 - 230" refId="ref7103" refString="Baker, J. G. (1895) CCCCLXXV. - Diagnoses africanae, VII. (continued from p. 153) [Kalanchoe somaliensis Baker on p. 214]. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information. Kew 1895: 211 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4114977" type="journal article" year="1895">Baker (1895: 214)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,986,2092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">
The locality from where material that prompted this change in rank was collected was given as “Hab.: « 
<collectingCountry name="Eritrea" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">Colonia Eritrea</collectingCountry>
. Altipiano del Soira (Scimenzana). Località Golò, 
<quantity box="[795,955,1130,1157]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.73" metricValueMax="2.7399999999999998" metricValueMin="2.7199999999999998" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" unit="m" value="2730.0" valueMax="2740.0" valueMin="2720.0">2720–2740 m</quantity>
. sul mare: ripiano alluvionale derivante dal disfacimento dell’arenaria. 
<date box="[450,644,1166,1193]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" value="1905-12-04">4 dicembre 1905</date>
[Dainelli e Marinelli] ».—(Herb. Centr. Florent. [Centr. extra-ital.]).” [English: “Colony of 
<collectingCountry box="[376,456,1202,1228]" name="Eritrea" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
. Soira Plateau (Scimenzana). Location Golò, 
<quantity box="[962,1117,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.73" metricValueMax="2.7399999999999998" metricValueMin="2.7199999999999998" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" unit="m" value="2730.0" valueMax="2740.0" valueMin="2720.0">2720–2740 m</quantity>
above sea level: alluvial shelf resulting from the decomposition of sandstone. 
<date box="[669,868,1238,1265]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" value="1905-12-04">4 December 1905</date>
[
<emphasis box="[884,1155,1238,1265]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">Danielli &amp; Marinelli s.n</emphasis>
.] (Herb. FI)”]. At the time this was regarded as the first and only record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1892" box="[699,860,1275,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[699,860,1275,1300]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1895" box="[911,1077,1274,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[911,1077,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, here regarded as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pampanini" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Baker" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marmorata" variety="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[1290,1451,1275,1300]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[184,315,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) known from beyond the borders of 
<collectingCountry box="[725,820,1310,1336]" name="Somalia" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, the country from which 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, J. G." box="[1100,1305,1310,1337]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="211 - 230" refId="ref7103" refString="Baker, J. G. (1895) CCCCLXXV. - Diagnoses africanae, VII. (continued from p. 153) [Kalanchoe somaliensis Baker on p. 214]. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information. Kew 1895: 211 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4114977" type="journal article" year="1895">Baker (1895: 214)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1895" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="somaliensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Golis range near Wardie (
<bibRefCitation author="Pampanini, R." box="[669,901,1346,1373]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="51 - 56" refId="ref9072" refString="Pampanini, R. (1909 [Febbraio]) Alcune Kalanchoe della Eritrea. Bullettino della SocietaI Botanica Italiana 1909 (2): 51 - 56. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 8551309  page / 345 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1909">Pampanini 1909: 54</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,986,2092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">
<collectorName box="[189,243,1383,1409]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">Note</collectorName>
that the specimen 
<emphasis box="[461,739,1382,1409]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">
<collectorName box="[461,553,1382,1408]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">Danielli</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectorName box="[592,698,1382,1408]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">Marinelli</collectorName>
s.n
</emphasis>
. is not the 
<typeStatus box="[870,918,1383,1409]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pampanini" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[959,1284,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" form="somaliensis" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[959,1119,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
f. 
<emphasis box="[1153,1284,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; it is merely a specimen that vouches for the occurrence of the forma in 
<collectingCountry box="[781,861,1418,1444]" name="Eritrea" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,986,2092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,1022,1454,1481]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">
Taxonomic and nomenclatural notes on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pampanini" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[667,1022,1454,1481]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marmorata" variety="somaliensis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[667,829,1455,1481]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[888,1022,1454,1481]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
:—When 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, J. G." box="[1132,1337,1454,1481]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="211 - 230" refId="ref7103" refString="Baker, J. G. (1895) CCCCLXXV. - Diagnoses africanae, VII. (continued from p. 153) [Kalanchoe somaliensis Baker on p. 214]. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information. Kew 1895: 211 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4114977" type="journal article" year="1895">Baker (1895: 214)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1895" box="[136,300,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[136,300,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
he gave the colour of the leaves as “brunneo-marmoratis” [brownish marbled] (see also the illustration published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, J. D." box="[292,445,1526,1552]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" refId="ref8318" refString="Hooker, J. D. (1902) Kalanchoe somaliensis. Native of Somaliland. Nat. Ord. Crassulaceae. Curtis's Botanical Magazine [, comprising the plants of the Royal Gardens of Kew, and of other botanical establishments in Great Britain; with suitable descriptions;] 3 rd ser., LVIII (volume CXXVIII of the whole work): Tab. 7831. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 14256  page / 75 / mode / 1 up]" type="url" year="1902">Hooker 1902</bibRefCitation>
), as opposed to the leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1892" box="[789,950,1527,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[789,950,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, J. G." box="[1011,1221,1526,1552]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" refId="ref6954" refString="Baker, J. G. (1892 [10 September]) New or noteworthy plants. Kalanchoe marmorata, Baker, n. sp. The Gardeners' Chronicle. [A weekly illustrated journal of Horticulture and Allied Subjects], 3 rd series, XII (No. 298) 300. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 83803  page / 316 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal volume" year="1892">Baker (1892: 300)</bibRefCitation>
earlier described as “maculis copiosis fuscis marmoratis” [copiously brown marbled spotted]. Therefore, material referable to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pampanini" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Baker" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marmorata" variety="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[1295,1451,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[184,315,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has leaves that are virtually throughout devoid of the characteristic purplish brown mottling found on one or both surfaces of the leaves of 
<taxonomicName authority="var. marmorata" box="[556,899,1635,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marmorata" variety="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[556,716,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[773,899,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The leaves of the autonymic 
<taxonomicName box="[1243,1362,1634,1661]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" rank="variety" variety="are">variety are</taxonomicName>
usually consistently sparsely to densely spotted with purplish brown marks and in some material can be lightly spotted only (see for example the discussion in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce, E. A." box="[523,657,1706,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="1049" refId="ref7407" refString="Bruce, E. A. (1948) Kalanchoe marmorata. Eritrea, Abyssinia, Somalia. Crassulaceae. The Flowering Plants of Africa 27: Plate 1049. https: // archive. org / details / floweringplantso 27 unse / page / n 45 / mode / 2 up" type="journal article" year="1948">Bruce 1948</bibRefCitation>
: t. 1049).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,986,2092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">
In his key, under “ 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[390,463,1742,1768]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">BaαI2</emphasis>
”, 
<bibRefCitation author="Berger, A." box="[488,690,1742,1769]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="402 - 412" refId="ref7207" refString="Berger, A. (1930 [Mai]) Crassulaceae. Unterfam. II. Kalanchoideae [sic, Kalanchooideae]. 6. Kalanchoe Adanson. 7. Kitchingia Baker. 8. Bryophyllum Salisb. In: Engler, A. &amp; Prantl, K. (Eds.) Die naturlichen Pflanzenfamilien. ed. 2, 18 a. Verlag von Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig, pp. 402 - 412." type="book chapter" year="1930">Berger (1930: 405</bibRefCitation>
and Figure 196 D–G on p. 403) additionally recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1895" box="[1289,1452,1742,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[1289,1452,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as being characterised by: “Röhre der Blumenkrone im oberen Teile zylindrisch. Blätter grosser, seichter buchtig gezähnt, fast weiss, einiger gefleckt”. [English: “Corolla tube cylindrical higher up. Leaves large, shallowly indented, almost white, somewhat maculate”]. The contrasting statement, “ 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[872,945,1850,1876]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">BaαI1</emphasis>
”, in the key provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Berger, A." box="[1236,1452,1850,1877]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="402 - 412" refId="ref7207" refString="Berger, A. (1930 [Mai]) Crassulaceae. Unterfam. II. Kalanchoideae [sic, Kalanchooideae]. 6. Kalanchoe Adanson. 7. Kitchingia Baker. 8. Bryophyllum Salisb. In: Engler, A. &amp; Prantl, K. (Eds.) Die naturlichen Pflanzenfamilien. ed. 2, 18 a. Verlag von Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig, pp. 402 - 412." type="book chapter" year="1930">Berger (1930: 405)</bibRefCitation>
noted: “Röhre der Blumenkrone 4kantig” for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1892" box="[645,803,1887,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[645,803,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, variation in the outline of cross-sections of the corolla tubes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1892" box="[317,476,1923,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[317,476,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been observed and this character is here not regarded as taxonomically useful.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,986,2092]" lastBlockId="8.[136,1452,158,329]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">
The leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pampanini" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[348,693,1958,1985]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marmorata" variety="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[348,506,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[562,693,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are often basally more distinctly amplexicaul and almost auriculate (see for example 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen, H." box="[341,573,1994,2020]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" refId="ref8443" refString="Jacobsen, H. (1977) Lexicon of succulent plants. Short descriptions, habitats and synonymy of succulent plants other than Cactaceae. Revised and enlarged 2 nd edn. Blandford Press, Poole, Dorset, 682 pp." type="book" year="1977">Jacobsen 1977: 289</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen, H." box="[588,707,1994,2021]" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" pagination="465 - 864" refId="ref8485" refString="Jacobsen, H. (1986) A handbook of succulent plants. Descriptions, synonyms and cultural details for succulents other than Cactaceae. Vol. II. Ficus to Zygophyllum. Blandford Press, Poole, Dorset, pp. 465 - 864." type="book chapter" year="1986">1986: 629</bibRefCitation>
) and not as cuneate as those of 
<taxonomicName authority="var. marmorata" box="[1093,1444,1995,2021]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marmorata" variety="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[1093,1255,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1318,1444,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pampanini" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[402,752,2030,2057]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marmorata" variety="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[402,562,2031,2056]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[621,752,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are often larger than those of 
<taxonomicName authority="var. marmorata" box="[1099,1444,2031,2057]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marmorata" variety="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[1099,1260,2031,2056]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1318,1444,2031,2056]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Taxonomic recognition of material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1892" box="[576,738,2067,2092]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[576,738,2067,2092]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="107">K. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with often larger, virtually immaculate, basally stem-clasping leaves seems desirable, as use of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1895" box="[620,784,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[620,784,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="108">K. somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, at the rank of species therefore, has persisted, for example in 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen, H." box="[165,407,194,220]" pageId="8" pageNumber="108" refId="ref8443" refString="Jacobsen, H. (1977) Lexicon of succulent plants. Short descriptions, habitats and synonymy of succulent plants other than Cactaceae. Revised and enlarged 2 nd edn. Blandford Press, Poole, Dorset, 682 pp." type="book" year="1977">Jacobsen (1977: 289)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen, H." box="[419,652,194,220]" pageId="8" pageNumber="108" pagination="465 - 864" refId="ref8485" refString="Jacobsen, H. (1986) A handbook of succulent plants. Descriptions, synonyms and cultural details for succulents other than Cactaceae. Vol. II. Ficus to Zygophyllum. Blandford Press, Poole, Dorset, pp. 465 - 864." type="book chapter" year="1986">Jacobsen (1986: 629</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 887), and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sajeva, M. &amp; Costanzo, M." box="[828,1181,194,221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="108" refId="ref9573" refString="Sajeva, M. &amp; Costanzo, M. (1994) Succulents. The new illustrated dictionary. Cassell plc, London, 239 pp." type="book" year="1994">Sajeva &amp; Costanzo (1994: 153)</bibRefCitation>
for material lacking the distinct purplish maculation. However, at the rank of variety a combination has only been made under 
<taxonomicName authority="Baker ex Maire" authorityName="Baker ex Maire" authorityYear="1976" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrantha">
<emphasis box="[1297,1451,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="108">K. macrantha</emphasis>
Baker ex Maire
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[320,437,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="108">nom. illeg.</emphasis>
Further, the nomenclatural novelty 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pampanini" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[831,1171,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="marmorata" variety="somaliensis">
<emphasis box="[831,988,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="108">K. marmorata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1040,1171,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="108">somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not a new combination as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pampanini" authorityYear="1909" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[166,486,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" form="somaliensis" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[166,325,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="108">K. marmorata</emphasis>
f. 
<emphasis box="[355,486,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="108">somaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been published previously (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[846,1065,302,329]" pageId="8" pageNumber="108" refId="ref10870" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Oberreifenberg. [Regnum Vegetabile 159]. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal volume" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[942,992,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="108">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 6.10 and its Example 13).
</paragraph>
